  "readingTitle": "tip — Paper 3 — Reading: spotting exceptions",
  "reading": "Examiners love testing el día, el mapa, el problema, el clima and la mano because they break the -o/-a rule. If a text uses 'el' before what looks like a feminine-shaped noun, check it isn't one of these classic exceptions before you answer.",
